CECA excludes a second fusion wave of the savings banks 
The general manager of the CECA, José Antonio Olavarrieta, rejected yesterday the possibility the fact that it could come to a fusion wave of the savings banks and stressed the speed, with which the industry is restructured. 
When the concentration process of the Spanish savings banks began to participate insisted several savings banks on it in the first phase not. They reserved themselves the second round. 
However the general manager of the Spanish association of savings banks (CECA) insured, José Antonio Olavarrieta, this second round would not take place. 
"I believe that the largest part of the fusions is final. The inclusion of Cajasol into the group of Banca Cívica cannot be regarded as the second round, it concerned rather adjustments." 
